Judging by the reference to the Sabine wine which Maecenas is invited to drink, and which came into use in its second year, reaching its prime in its fourth, the poem would have been written between two , and four years after the reception that the audience at the theatre gave to Maecenas on his recovery from his illness. But the date of that event ,is not determined. Franke and Liibker refer the composition of the ode to A.U.C. 729-7 30. Macleane favours the latter year. Orelli inclines to Weber's date, from A.u.c. 726-727.
